SCENE 2 (627—728). Lysiteles urges Lesbonicus to give him his sister without dowry. Lesbonicus refuses on the ground that to do so would be a disgrace to himself. Stasimus listens unseen to the argu- ment until v, 705, when he declares the victory in argument to lie with

Lysiteles. But neither young man will give way, and Stasimus is left lamenting.
